Vendored third-party software

This project includes the following third-party components. The C engine
(libyang, PCRE2) is vendored under `third_party/` and statically linked by the
optional backend. The pure-Go YANG parser is a vendored copy of openconfig/goyang
under `go/internal/yangparse/upstream/`.

## goyang (openconfig/goyang)

- Location: `go/internal/yangparse/upstream`
- Upstream: https://github.com/openconfig/goyang
- Version: v1.6.3 (tag SHA 274b3b50006c99113ae0670d8d250a4d093536cb)
- License: Apache-2.0
- Copyright: Google Inc.

Cambium's default pure-Go schema package uses a vendored copy of goyang's
`pkg/yang` and `pkg/indent` as its cgo-free YANG parser, so the default Go
package has no runtime dependency on the upstream module. The copied source
retains its upstream Apache-2.0 license headers; the full license text is at
`go/internal/yangparse/upstream/LICENSE`. Cambium modified some of these files;
the changes are documented in `go/internal/yangparse/upstream/UPSTREAM.md`.

## libyang

- Location: `third_party/libyang`
- Upstream: https://github.com/CESNET/libyang
- License: BSD-3-Clause
- Copyright: CESNET, 2015-2025

libyang is the RFC 7950 YANG engine used by Cambium. The pinned version is
recorded in `/VERSIONS`.

## PCRE2

- Location: `third_party/pcre2`
- Upstream: https://github.com/PCRE2Project/pcre2
- License: BSD-2-Clause (with JIT compilation support under the same terms)
- Copyright: University of Cambridge, 1997-2024; Zoltan Herczeg, 2010-2024

PCRE2 is the regular-expression engine required by libyang. The pinned version
is recorded in `/VERSIONS`.
